import React, {Fragment} from "react"
import Card from 'react-bootstrap/Card'
import Button from "react-bootstrap/Button"
const CardTrial = () => {
return (
    <Fragment>
    <Card style={{ width: '18rem' }}>
    <Card.Img variant="top" src="https://media-exp1.licdn.com/dms/image/C5103AQHhYDGGlRQvCg/profile-displayphoto-shrink_200_200/0?e=1597276800&v=beta&t=tARkwOTNoJTISBP3DN6osB421rBQU8b7NdNK7I4PI_Q" />
    <Card.Body>
      <Card.Title>Card Title</Card.Title>
      <Card.Text>
        Some quick example text to build on the card title and make up the bulk of
        the card's content.
      </Card.Text>
      <Button variant="primary">Go somewhere</Button>
    </Card.Body>
  </Card>
  </Fragment>
)
}

export default CardTrial;
